Description: Fragment of neck of Klazomenian black-figured pottery neck-amphora. Part of large palmette; added red for outline of inner section, added white dots in outer.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Temple of Aphrodite (Naukratis), Context Φ5(?) (?)
Curator's comments: This sherd is labelled in pencil Φ5 (however the first character is obscured and unclear), designating this as coming from a context within the temple of Aphrodite, during Gardner’s excavations at Naukratis in 1885-1886.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GH.144)
